WEBVTT

00:02.836 --> 00:04.172
All right,
let's focus up.

00:04.205 --> 00:07.875
It's a car wash,
not a car chitchat, 'kay?

00:07.908 --> 00:11.845
* No one knows what it's like,
knows the hell you -- *

00:11.879 --> 00:13.747
[ Music stops ]
Nice trash barge, Ang.

00:13.781 --> 00:15.683
Give me a break.
90% of my meals

00:15.716 --> 00:16.984
are consumed
at a red light.

00:17.017 --> 00:18.052
What do you want
from me?

00:18.086 --> 00:19.720
What was that music?
Is that grunge?

00:19.753 --> 00:21.222
That new grunge thing?

00:21.255 --> 00:22.856
It's heavy metal.
Whatever.

00:22.890 --> 00:24.658
In high school,
I was a big Korn fan.

00:24.692 --> 00:26.394
Korn?! [ Laughs ]

00:26.427 --> 00:28.762
That's -- That's not --
That's not funny at all.

00:28.796 --> 00:30.731
Mom always wanted
to be in a metal band!

00:30.764 --> 00:32.766
She wanted to learn
how to play guitar.

00:32.800 --> 00:34.835
But then I was born,

00:34.868 --> 00:37.037
and, as she put it,
the fun died.

00:37.071 --> 00:38.706
No, I never said that!

00:38.739 --> 00:40.874
And yeah, so what?
I love metal.

00:40.908 --> 00:42.743
Makes me feel
like a demon's inside me,

00:42.776 --> 00:43.877
and I like that.

00:43.911 --> 00:46.514
But, anyway,
none of you guys understand.

00:46.547 --> 00:47.681
You're too happy.

00:47.715 --> 00:50.017
I love you, G.
Now go play with some trash.

00:50.050 --> 00:51.385
Yes!

00:51.419 --> 00:53.454
Whoa, look at the sky.
Storm's a-brewing.

00:53.487 --> 00:56.257
I definitely got to
check this out back
at the weather center.

00:56.290 --> 00:57.291
You mean
your kitchen counter?

00:57.325 --> 00:58.359
[ Tires squeal, horn honks ]

00:58.392 --> 01:00.228
Douglas: Is that --
That is.

01:00.261 --> 01:01.262
Big Red.

01:01.295 --> 01:02.463
That chick
that blew you off

01:02.496 --> 01:03.964
'cause she saw you
dressed as a chipmunk?

01:03.997 --> 01:06.234
Yes.
Isn't she extraordinary?

01:07.067 --> 01:09.537
[ Cart squeaks, wheels clatter ]

01:09.570 --> 01:11.372
Douglas, you can't be
that obsessed with someone

01:11.405 --> 01:13.107
based off
physical appearance.

01:13.141 --> 01:15.109
Love is about making
an emotional connection.

01:15.143 --> 01:16.377
How's that
working out for ya?

01:16.410 --> 01:18.612
Eh, you want a prince,
you gotta kiss some frogs.

01:18.646 --> 01:20.548
And this month,
I've kissed two frogs,

01:20.581 --> 01:21.782
one with man buns.

01:21.815 --> 01:23.117
Big Red is no frog.

01:23.151 --> 01:24.285
Come, Miggy.
I'm gonna need you

01:24.318 --> 01:25.453
to run a screen
for the friend

01:25.486 --> 01:26.720
while I make my move.

01:26.754 --> 01:28.622
I got you.
You my road dawg.

01:28.656 --> 01:30.658
Meaningless.
Let's go.

01:30.691 --> 01:31.925
And lose the hat,
okay?

01:31.959 --> 01:34.462
We're not shagging
foul balls.

01:34.495 --> 01:36.297
You got your purse?

01:36.330 --> 01:37.798
Uh, excuse me.
Haven't we met?

01:37.831 --> 01:40.067
Hi,
I-I'm Dr. Douglas Fogerty.

01:40.100 --> 01:42.570
I'm co-owner
of a 40-foot houseboat,

01:42.603 --> 01:44.372
along with
Dennis Franz.

01:45.339 --> 01:46.474
Chipmunk!
How are ya?

01:46.507 --> 01:47.808
[ Chuckles ] Good.

01:47.841 --> 01:49.777
This is Judy. We work together
at the travel agency.

01:49.810 --> 01:52.946
I'm Miggy, and I do not know
what a travel agency is.

01:52.980 --> 01:54.014
[ Chuckles ]

01:54.047 --> 01:55.916
Oh, what a cute baby.

01:55.949 --> 01:59.119
Listen, if you ever want
a man to buy you dinner

01:59.153 --> 02:01.455
or a small casino
in Biloxi,

02:01.489 --> 02:02.856
you know
where to find me.

02:02.890 --> 02:03.991
Okay, Chipmunk.

02:04.024 --> 02:06.360
C'mon, Judy.
Mama needs her midday Cobb.

02:06.394 --> 02:07.795
Sorry you blew that.

02:07.828 --> 02:09.297
Please.
I nailed it.

02:09.330 --> 02:10.331
Big Red:
Hey, Chipmunk!

02:10.364 --> 02:11.699
[ Chuckles ]

02:11.732 --> 02:15.203
I think we both feel the sparks
that are flying here.

02:15.236 --> 02:18.306
The electricity is
in the air.

02:18.339 --> 02:20.341
So how are we gonna get
Judy and Miggy together?

02:20.374 --> 02:21.842
I mean,
she's just gaga for him.

02:21.875 --> 02:23.377
For Miggy?

02:23.411 --> 02:24.778
He's six feet of useless

02:24.812 --> 02:27.047
stuffed in a ball cap
and gym shorts.

02:28.682 --> 02:33.454
I-I mean, he --
he's a very...special man,

02:33.487 --> 02:35.022
so maybe
the four of us

02:35.055 --> 02:36.957
can have an elegant dinner
at my home.

02:36.990 --> 02:38.792
Sophie:
Car's ready!

02:38.826 --> 02:42.963
Ah, my very expensive,
very foreign sedan

02:42.996 --> 02:44.298
seems to be ready.

02:44.332 --> 02:45.866
Gratuity's not included!

02:45.899 --> 02:46.967
You should've
thought of that

02:47.000 --> 02:49.303
when you half-assed
the vacuuming job!

02:49.337 --> 02:50.471
**

02:50.504 --> 02:51.472
Children.

02:51.505 --> 02:54.808
-- Captions by VITAC --

02:54.842 --> 02:58.145
**

02:58.178 --> 03:00.481
Hey. You texted me
you had a surprise?

03:00.514 --> 03:01.649
Huge news.

03:01.682 --> 03:03.884
There's a tropical storm
moving up the coast.

03:03.917 --> 03:05.586
Check out this action.

03:05.619 --> 03:06.587
I-I have no idea

03:06.620 --> 03:07.588
what I'm looking at.

03:07.621 --> 03:08.689
What you're looking at

03:08.722 --> 03:10.691
is a very intense
low-pressure wind system

03:10.724 --> 03:12.526
that's forming
over a tropical ocean --

03:12.560 --> 03:14.027
a cyclone.

03:14.061 --> 03:15.696
So I guess we like
different stuff, huh?

03:15.729 --> 03:17.331
You know, I used to chase
these monsters

03:17.365 --> 03:18.899
back when I was a producer
at the Weather Channel.

03:18.932 --> 03:21.369
They always threw me into
the most dangerous situations,

03:21.402 --> 03:22.736
like hurricanes
and snowstorms,

03:22.770 --> 03:25.439
thunder so loud, it would
change a dog's personality.

03:25.473 --> 03:28.576
But The Beast,
he wasn't afraid of nothing.

03:28.609 --> 03:30.578
You've been wearing an oven mitt
the whole time I've been here.

03:30.611 --> 03:31.579
Oh! Right, sorry!

03:31.612 --> 03:33.180
I made brownies!
Ah.

03:33.213 --> 03:34.582
You know, Will, I'm gonna go,

03:34.615 --> 03:36.216
But thanks so much
for the surprise.

03:36.250 --> 03:37.285
You really get me.

03:37.318 --> 03:38.686
That's not your surprise.

03:38.719 --> 03:40.721
This is your surprise.

03:40.754 --> 03:41.889
[ Guitar flourish plays ]

03:41.922 --> 03:43.424
You signed me up
for a guitar lesson?

03:43.457 --> 03:45.058
Mm-hmm.
What am I, your kid?

03:45.092 --> 03:48.462
I don't know. Is my kid
a demon-worshipping headbanger?

03:48.496 --> 03:50.298
[ Deep voice ] * Da-Da-Da-Da-
Da-Da-Da-Da-Darkness *

03:50.331 --> 03:52.132
* Blood

03:52.165 --> 03:54.568
* Satan is
a close personal friend *

03:54.602 --> 03:57.104
Thanks a lot,
but I-I-I can't do this.

03:57.137 --> 03:58.939
I have a job and a child.

03:58.972 --> 04:01.208
The closest thing I have
to personal time is

04:01.241 --> 04:03.311
the walk from my house
to the car in the morning

04:03.344 --> 04:04.445
where,
for seven or eight seconds,

04:04.478 --> 04:06.246
I can just let everything go
and chew gum.

04:06.280 --> 04:07.315
Come on!

04:07.348 --> 04:08.949
I saw your face
back at the car wash.

04:08.982 --> 04:11.385
You were so happy
talking about being in a band.

04:11.419 --> 04:12.586
You were even happier

04:12.620 --> 04:14.388
than the time you ordered
regular-size fries

04:14.422 --> 04:16.290
and they actually brought you
large fries instead.

04:16.324 --> 04:18.292
I do love free stuff.
Who doesn't?

04:18.326 --> 04:21.295
All right.
I'll take the lesson.

04:21.329 --> 04:23.263
We're gonna make
so much slime tonight.

04:23.297 --> 04:25.499
We're gonna destroy
your house, Rory.

04:25.533 --> 04:27.935
I like when the slime
sounds like farts.

04:27.968 --> 04:28.836
[ Giggles ]

04:28.869 --> 04:30.304
The things we do
for these kids.

04:30.338 --> 04:31.472
Eyes on the prize,
Sophie.

04:31.505 --> 04:32.840
Remember what we
get to do tonight.

04:32.873 --> 04:34.975
We put them to sleep
and then hit season two

04:35.008 --> 04:36.644
of "BBC Presents:
Sir Bridger."

04:36.677 --> 04:38.178
Do you think
Sir Bridger will accept

04:38.211 --> 04:39.747
Lady Agnes'
marriage proposal?

04:39.780 --> 04:41.114
Please.

04:41.148 --> 04:43.784
He knows she's a modern woman,
and he loves it.

04:43.817 --> 04:45.285
Yes, he does.

04:45.319 --> 04:46.587
All right,
open mic is set up.

04:46.620 --> 04:48.622
Okay, kids, let's go.

04:48.656 --> 04:55.262
**

04:55.295 --> 04:56.797
[ Chuckles nervously ]

04:56.830 --> 04:58.131
**

04:58.165 --> 04:59.600
Damn.

04:59.633 --> 05:00.601
Lightning.

05:00.634 --> 05:01.835
**

05:01.869 --> 05:02.836
[ Chuckles lightly ]

05:02.870 --> 05:04.705
Mama, let's go!

05:04.738 --> 05:06.306
Graham out here
gettin' restless.

05:06.340 --> 05:07.641
[ Softly ]
Okay, okay.

05:07.675 --> 05:09.142
Zam!

05:09.176 --> 05:10.778
Thanks for
the threads, man.

05:10.811 --> 05:13.180
Ah, I feel so weird.
I feel like someone's dad.

05:13.213 --> 05:14.147
You are.

05:14.181 --> 05:15.148
So, what's the occasion?

05:15.182 --> 05:16.550
I want you
to have dinner with me.

05:16.584 --> 05:17.951
You asking me on a date?

05:17.985 --> 05:18.786
Okay.

05:18.819 --> 05:20.187
Why would you
say yes to that?

05:20.220 --> 05:23.857
It's a double date
with Big Red and her friend.

05:23.891 --> 05:26.293
Apparently she's "gaga."
For Miggy?

05:26.326 --> 05:28.629
Yeah, I agree.
It's insane.

05:28.662 --> 05:31.565
But this is the only way
to move the chains with Big Red,

05:31.599 --> 05:33.000
so I need you.

05:33.033 --> 05:35.202
Nah, I can't go out
with another woman.

05:35.235 --> 05:36.236
I got Zara.

05:36.269 --> 05:38.572
Tony,
take a soft five.

05:38.606 --> 05:40.073
All right.

05:40.107 --> 05:42.075
What's the deal
with you and that broad?

05:42.109 --> 05:43.010
Are you a couple?

05:43.043 --> 05:44.378
Nah, we're
in the gray gray.

05:44.412 --> 05:46.213
English, please.

05:46.246 --> 05:48.682
Well, some days,
I feel like we're friends,

05:48.716 --> 05:51.218
and some days,
we're hooking up!

05:51.251 --> 05:53.086
[ Chuckles ]
You know, the gray gray.

05:53.120 --> 05:54.655
Just tell me --
what do you want?

05:54.688 --> 05:56.256
I don't know.

05:56.289 --> 05:57.391
I love her.

05:57.425 --> 05:58.692
I want to be with her.

05:58.726 --> 06:00.093
Okay.

06:00.127 --> 06:02.930
What do you know
about women and shopping?

06:02.963 --> 06:03.897
They like it?

06:03.931 --> 06:05.198
They love it!

06:05.232 --> 06:06.567
And do you know
how to get a woman

06:06.600 --> 06:08.368
to shop in your store?

06:08.402 --> 06:10.404
Uh, you put the word "lady"
in front of it,

06:10.438 --> 06:11.572
like Lady Foot Locker?

06:11.605 --> 06:14.442
No! You put your best dress
in the window.

06:14.475 --> 06:15.709
You following me?

06:15.743 --> 06:18.278
You're the dress.
You got to sell yourself.

06:18.311 --> 06:19.279
How do I do that?

06:19.312 --> 06:20.948
By making Zara jealous.

06:20.981 --> 06:24.618
If Zara sees you with this Judy,
she will fight for you.

06:24.652 --> 06:25.586
You trust me.

06:25.619 --> 06:28.121
Okay. I'll go
on a date with you.

06:28.155 --> 06:30.791
Yo,
is your tailor dead?

06:30.824 --> 06:31.992
Nah,
just nudge him.

06:33.326 --> 06:35.262
Ah! Oh.
Ah!

06:35.295 --> 06:36.930
He does this
all the time.

06:36.964 --> 06:38.966
It's why he doesn't
drive for me anymore.

06:38.999 --> 06:42.135
**

06:42.169 --> 06:43.537
[ Monitor beeps ]
Ugh.

06:43.571 --> 06:45.573
Well, congrats.

06:45.606 --> 06:48.776
I went to your dumb guitar
lesson and got mom-shamed.

06:48.809 --> 06:51.545
Wait, you're taking the lesson,
not Graham?

06:51.579 --> 06:54.114
She's having me-time.
God, I wish I could do that.

06:54.147 --> 06:55.949
I took a yoga class
four years ago.

06:55.983 --> 06:57.618
I still think about
how I could've spent that time

06:57.651 --> 06:58.952
getting to know my kid.

06:58.986 --> 07:01.622
One second, they're your baby,
and the next, they leave you.

07:01.655 --> 07:03.123
But you should
take guitar!

07:03.156 --> 07:04.224
Totally.

07:04.257 --> 07:06.460
It sounds like they were
just being supportive.

07:06.494 --> 07:07.795
You don't get it, man.

07:07.828 --> 07:09.963
Moms are allowed
to do two things --

07:09.997 --> 07:11.298
work and raise kids.

07:11.331 --> 07:13.734
And if a mom catches you
doing something for yourself,

07:13.767 --> 07:16.103
she's gonna be like,
"You go, girl,"

07:16.136 --> 07:18.739
but what she really means is,
"You're a bad mom,"

07:18.772 --> 07:20.641
and not the cool kind,
like in the movies.

07:20.674 --> 07:22.610
Just because you have a kid
doesn't mean you suddenly have

07:22.643 --> 07:24.512
to give up everything you ever
wanted to do with your life.

07:24.545 --> 07:26.680
[ Monitor beeps ]
Oh!
Yeah. Okay.

07:26.714 --> 07:28.281
Except you love weather,

07:28.315 --> 07:30.150
and yet you're sitting here
at your kitchen counter

07:30.183 --> 07:31.318
staring
at computer screens.

07:31.351 --> 07:32.653
Isn't weather outside?

07:32.686 --> 07:35.122
Dude, I'm still getting the
weather high inside the house.

07:35.155 --> 07:36.624
I'm currently tracking
highs and lows

07:36.657 --> 07:38.358
on no less than
three online Dopplers --

07:38.391 --> 07:40.293
Okay, so you're saying
that you are just as happy

07:40.327 --> 07:42.129
working from home
as you were out in the field?

07:42.162 --> 07:43.831
Yeah.
You don't miss
storm watching?

07:43.864 --> 07:44.865
No.
Chasing hurricanes?

07:44.898 --> 07:45.799
No.
Floods?

07:45.833 --> 07:47.000
Wet.
Ice caps melting?

07:47.034 --> 07:49.002
Well, that's a global thing.
That's not really weather.

07:49.036 --> 07:50.137
It's true. It's not lies.
That's manmade problems.

07:50.170 --> 07:52.005
Yeah, we're on the same page
with that.

07:52.039 --> 07:53.707
So you don't miss
being The Beast?

07:53.741 --> 07:56.176
I...do not.

07:56.209 --> 08:00.514
My Beast was very humanely
and gently euthanized.

08:00.548 --> 08:01.949
He had his time, okay,

08:01.982 --> 08:03.483
but I am trying
to create that time

08:03.517 --> 08:04.718
for you now, Angie.

08:04.752 --> 08:06.954
You're right.
I --

08:06.987 --> 08:09.056
I'm gonna go back
to the guitar place.
Good.

08:09.089 --> 08:11.391
Would you come with me
for moral support?

08:11.424 --> 08:12.960
Just try and stop me.

08:12.993 --> 08:14.327
**

08:14.361 --> 08:15.863
And just so you know,
the moral support

08:15.896 --> 08:17.230
isn't limited
to the drive.

08:17.264 --> 08:18.632
I'm happy to walk you
into your classroom.

08:18.666 --> 08:20.300
I'd love to meet
your teacher.

08:20.333 --> 08:21.835
Huh.
That's weird.

08:21.869 --> 08:24.538
We're nowhere near
the guitar school.
Where are we going?

08:24.572 --> 08:25.673
To the storm.

08:25.706 --> 08:26.807
What?!
Are you insane?!

08:26.840 --> 08:28.041
You push me,
I'm pushing you!

08:28.075 --> 08:29.977
Angie,
it is a cyclone!

08:30.010 --> 08:31.979
[ Heavy metal music playing ]

08:32.012 --> 08:35.649
* It's a cyclooooooone

08:35.683 --> 08:38.018
* Bow down to its power

08:38.051 --> 08:40.087
Aaaaaaah!

08:40.120 --> 08:41.755
I'm just gonna lower this
a little bit.

08:41.789 --> 08:43.757
No! Don't touch it.
Okay. Sure, Will.

08:43.791 --> 08:46.159
Let's buy Angie a guitar lesson.
Where's the harm in that?

08:46.193 --> 08:47.394
**

08:51.799 --> 08:53.033
Angie, turn around.
This is crazy, okay?

08:53.066 --> 08:54.434
Your minivan is not equipped
for this kind of weather.

08:54.467 --> 08:56.536
This is dangerous.
I'll turn around,
as soon as you admit

08:56.570 --> 08:58.071
that you miss
being out in the field.

08:58.105 --> 09:00.708
Yes, fine. I admit it, okay?
I miss it.

09:00.741 --> 09:01.942
I miss it every day.

09:01.975 --> 09:03.410
So, then,
why did you quit?

09:03.443 --> 09:05.445
The Beast,
he could be reckless.

09:05.478 --> 09:07.681
I highly doubt
that you could be reckless.

09:07.715 --> 09:08.782
Oh, yeah?

09:08.816 --> 09:10.584
Tell that to Glen.

09:10.618 --> 09:12.119
[ Thunder crashes ]
We didn't get
the shot, Glen!

09:12.152 --> 09:15.122
Let's head for the shelter!
This is suicide!

09:15.155 --> 09:16.189
Sack up, girlie!

09:16.223 --> 09:17.124
I'm counting you in

09:17.157 --> 09:18.859
in three, two...
[ News cue plays ]

09:18.892 --> 09:22.262
This is Glen Seabreeze
reporting liiii--

09:22.295 --> 09:23.964
Glennnnnnn!
[ News cue plays ]

09:23.997 --> 09:25.365
Oh, my God!
He died?!

09:25.398 --> 09:28.936
No! We found him on a roof,
like, a mile away. He's fine.

09:28.969 --> 09:31.271
Anyway, after that,
it just sort of felt like

09:31.304 --> 09:33.907
it was irresponsible to have
such a dangerous job, you know?

09:33.941 --> 09:35.743
I-I'm Sophie's
only parent.

09:35.776 --> 09:37.711
Unless you count
a crazy woman

09:37.745 --> 09:39.412
living in the Sudan
with no cell service.

09:39.446 --> 09:41.048
Look, I get it, okay?

09:41.081 --> 09:42.650
We both had kids,
and we gave up on our dreams.

09:42.683 --> 09:44.417
Except my dream was cool.

09:44.451 --> 09:45.318
Look out!
Aah!

09:45.352 --> 09:46.887
[ Tires squeal ]
[ Both scream ]

09:46.920 --> 09:48.088
[ Bang ]
Oh!
Aah!

09:48.121 --> 09:49.322
Are you okay?
Are you okay?
Yeah.

09:49.356 --> 09:51.458
All right, let's back it up.
Back up very slowly.

09:51.491 --> 09:52.993
[ Engine revs, tire squeals ]

09:53.026 --> 09:55.128
Give it more gas.
I'm hitting the gas!

09:55.162 --> 09:57.297
It's not working!
We're stuck!

09:57.330 --> 09:59.800
Will, what do we do?
We don't panic.

09:59.833 --> 10:01.601
We stay calm...

10:01.635 --> 10:03.971
as your minivan is ripped apart
piece by piece.

10:04.004 --> 10:04.772
What?!

10:04.805 --> 10:07.941
[ Thunder crashes ]

10:07.975 --> 10:09.309
* I can't deny

10:09.342 --> 10:11.478
I'm glad we were able
to do this.

10:11.511 --> 10:13.246
I think
I parked on your lawn.

10:13.280 --> 10:15.949
And what a lucky lawn
that is.

10:15.983 --> 10:16.984
[ Mouth full ]
Where's Miggy?

10:17.017 --> 10:18.451
Y-You know what --
I don't know

10:18.485 --> 10:19.687
what --
what's keeping him.

10:19.720 --> 10:20.821
But I here,

10:20.854 --> 10:24.424
and I have a very elegant
meal prepared.

10:24.457 --> 10:26.293
Tony,
how's the prime rib?

10:26.326 --> 10:27.294
[ Electric knife whirs ]

10:27.327 --> 10:28.295
[ Doorbell rings ]

10:28.328 --> 10:29.362
Oh.

10:29.396 --> 10:31.932
Excuse me.
That's probably him.

10:31.965 --> 10:33.500
**

10:33.533 --> 10:36.036
Thicker, man.
This isn't a deli.

10:36.069 --> 10:40.007
* Chasing, it's a silly...

10:40.040 --> 10:41.274
[ Whispering ] Where the hell
have you been?

10:41.308 --> 10:43.310
Come on.
Sorry I'm late, Douglas.

10:43.343 --> 10:44.812
How's it going
with Big Red?
[ Door closes ]

10:44.845 --> 10:46.446
Listen, we're not
out of the blocks yet.

10:46.479 --> 10:48.548
I only have
so much cocktail banter.

10:48.581 --> 10:50.851
I was just about to break out
pictures of my kids.

10:50.884 --> 10:51.852
Like some chump.

10:51.885 --> 10:54.688
Wha-- What's with
the sour puss?

10:54.722 --> 10:56.623
I texted Zara
to check on Jack,

10:56.656 --> 10:58.625
and I told her I was going
on a date tonight,

10:58.658 --> 11:00.460
and she didn't care.

11:00.493 --> 11:02.195
She's happy
I'm getting out there.

11:02.229 --> 11:04.397
I-I-I don't get it.
You said she'd be jealous.

11:04.431 --> 11:05.999
Ah, I say
a lot of things.

11:06.033 --> 11:08.535
Now, let's bring these lobsters
to a boil, huh?

11:08.568 --> 11:09.636
I don't know, Douglas.

11:09.669 --> 11:10.971
Look, I'm sorry
to leave you hanging,

11:11.004 --> 11:12.572
but maybe
I should go home...

11:12.605 --> 11:14.708
[ Chuckles ] No,
you're not going anywhere.

11:14.742 --> 11:16.209
Miggy, listen to me.

11:16.243 --> 11:18.846
Ever since I became a man
at age 9,

11:18.879 --> 11:20.513
I've never had
a problem with women,

11:20.547 --> 11:23.817
but tonight, I think Big Red
is gonna make me dance for it.

11:23.851 --> 11:27.921
Now, the only thing she and Judy
seem to like about me is you,

11:27.955 --> 11:31.658
so I need you to get out there
and help me land this plane.

11:31.691 --> 11:32.659
[ Inhales sharply ]

11:32.692 --> 11:34.762
Okay. Yeah.
I can do this.

11:34.795 --> 11:36.029
Let's go sell
some dresses.

11:36.063 --> 11:36.997
Okay, thatta boy.

11:37.030 --> 11:38.231
And for God's sakes,
lose the hat.

11:38.265 --> 11:40.567
This isn't
a Spike Lee joint, okay?

11:40.600 --> 11:43.837
Here he is!
Your man of the hour!

11:43.871 --> 11:44.905
Eh?

11:44.938 --> 11:46.173
How are you?

11:46.206 --> 11:49.042
Pfft.

11:49.076 --> 11:51.211
The mother of my child
is fine with me dating,

11:51.244 --> 11:52.279
and I don't want to live!

11:52.312 --> 11:54.414
Oh, you poor baby!

11:54.447 --> 11:56.183
Oh, okay, okay.
Put your head right here.

11:56.216 --> 11:57.617
Come on.
You want a butterscotch?

11:57.650 --> 11:59.252
Miggy: [ Muffled ]
Yes, please.

11:59.286 --> 12:02.455
Lady Everson put the arsenic
in Sir Bridger's pipe?

12:02.489 --> 12:04.892
She hates
that he'll never love her.

12:04.925 --> 12:05.893
Hm.

12:05.926 --> 12:07.394
Poppy, where are you?

12:07.427 --> 12:09.096
The lights are on,
but nobody's home.

12:09.129 --> 12:10.964
Okay, I feel like
you're bizarrely mature,

12:10.998 --> 12:13.400
so I can share this
with you.

12:13.433 --> 12:16.269
I saw that keyboard player
at the Winebrary,

12:16.303 --> 12:18.038
and ol' Poppy lost it.

12:18.071 --> 12:19.439
Mmm! Lightning.

12:19.472 --> 12:21.408
That rando
from the open mic night?

12:21.441 --> 12:22.275
Mm-hmm.

12:22.309 --> 12:23.543
Girl, we gotta talk.

12:23.576 --> 12:26.046
I felt a connection.
He's a deep soul.

12:26.079 --> 12:28.215
I bet he toils at his day job
as a volunteer nurse

12:28.248 --> 12:30.450
so that by night, he can explore
his real passion --

12:30.483 --> 12:33.086
bringing jazz keyboard
to the masses.

12:33.120 --> 12:34.822
* Bippity-bop-bop,
bitty, bop, bop *

12:34.855 --> 12:36.957
Baaaaa-- Oww!

12:36.990 --> 12:38.425
Where are you
getting all of this?

12:38.458 --> 12:39.759
I felt a connection.

12:39.793 --> 12:42.295
Then why not go
to the Winebrary? Talk to him?

12:42.329 --> 12:43.931
What am I gonna do,
leave you kids alone?

12:43.964 --> 12:46.800
Look, it's what we parents do.
We sacrifice.

12:46.834 --> 12:48.268
Not when
it comes to love!

12:48.301 --> 12:50.237
Do you know who ignored
his heart, Poppy?

12:50.270 --> 12:51.404
Lord Chigwell.

12:51.438 --> 12:53.406
He could've stopped the wedding,
but he didn't.

12:53.440 --> 12:54.774
And what happened?

12:54.808 --> 12:56.977
He got his face burned off
by a steam engine.

12:57.010 --> 12:58.311
He did?!
Yes!

12:58.345 --> 13:00.447
* It was incredible!

13:00.480 --> 13:02.149
I won't let you
make the same mistake.

13:02.182 --> 13:03.951
**

13:03.984 --> 13:06.153
All right, guys,
put down the slime.

13:06.186 --> 13:08.788
We gotta help Poppy connect
with the man of her dreams.

13:08.822 --> 13:09.957
I'm the man
of her dreams.

13:09.990 --> 13:11.458
And we connect
all the time.

13:11.491 --> 13:13.293
[ Pbhhht! ]
That was
a good one.

13:13.326 --> 13:15.328
Guys. Poppy needs us.

13:15.362 --> 13:18.365
There's a man out there who she
thinks could be her soul mate.

13:18.398 --> 13:19.799
Fine.

13:19.833 --> 13:22.669
It's not every woman
I'll put down my slime for.

13:22.702 --> 13:27.474
But, Poppy, for you,
I'll do anything.

13:27.507 --> 13:29.542
**

13:29.576 --> 13:30.978
Oh, yes.

13:31.011 --> 13:39.152
**

13:39.186 --> 13:47.294
**

13:47.327 --> 13:48.295
Oh.

13:48.328 --> 13:50.898
I better do this
myself.

13:52.332 --> 13:53.666
Oh, my God!
There's so much rain!

13:53.700 --> 13:56.069
Yeah, well, welcome
to a Category 2 storm, Angie.

13:56.103 --> 13:57.137
Agh!
It's over.

13:57.170 --> 13:58.805
I hope you've made peace
with your god.

13:58.838 --> 14:01.141
You know what we need
right now, Will?

14:01.174 --> 14:02.675
We need The Beast!

14:02.709 --> 14:05.478
Angie, The Beast is dead.
I told you that.

14:05.512 --> 14:06.846
I had this friend Glen --

14:06.880 --> 14:08.882
I know the Glen story!

14:08.916 --> 14:11.018
Show me The Beast!

14:12.052 --> 14:13.753
Okay, okay.
[ Seatbelt clicks ]

14:13.786 --> 14:14.854
We're gonna
get out of this car,

14:14.888 --> 14:16.489
we're gonna throw
this bad boy in neutral,

14:16.523 --> 14:17.925
and we're gonna push it
out of the mud to freedom.

14:17.958 --> 14:19.426
No!
Yes! Now, when you
get out there...

14:19.459 --> 14:21.761
[ Whimpers ]
...take a very wide,
very strong stance.

14:21.794 --> 14:24.431
I can't get out of this car!
It's too hardcore!

14:24.464 --> 14:25.598
[ Deep voice ]
You're hardcore!

14:25.632 --> 14:27.400
[ Heavy metal music plays ]
Aah!

14:27.434 --> 14:29.102
I love this song!

14:29.136 --> 14:31.204
**

14:31.238 --> 14:33.106
Aaaaaagh!

14:33.140 --> 14:36.176
All right, get low,
bend with your knees, and push!

14:36.209 --> 14:38.745
I'm using my knees!
What else would I be using?!

14:38.778 --> 14:40.413
Okay, one, two, three!

14:40.447 --> 14:42.882
Aah!
Yeah!

14:42.916 --> 14:44.451
Yeah!

14:44.484 --> 14:46.086
[ Laughs ]
Whoo!

14:46.119 --> 14:46.886
Aah!

14:46.920 --> 14:47.887
Okay!

14:47.921 --> 14:49.689
[ Music continues, muffled ]

14:49.722 --> 14:52.725
[ Music continues, loud ]

14:52.759 --> 14:54.761
[ Thunder crashes ]

14:54.794 --> 14:56.829
[ Wind howling ]

15:02.835 --> 15:05.138
[ Thunder crashes ]

15:29.997 --> 15:31.031
No! Angie!

15:35.368 --> 15:36.436
I thought
we'd end up together.

15:36.469 --> 15:37.937
We're best friends.
We have a baby.

15:37.971 --> 15:40.007
How is she cool
with me dating?

15:40.040 --> 15:41.308
Well,
give it some time.

15:41.341 --> 15:42.976
She'll realize
what she's missing.

15:43.010 --> 15:44.811
Nuts to that.
Let's go cut her.

15:44.844 --> 15:48.148
Miggy, can I, uh, console you
in the next room, huh?

15:48.181 --> 15:49.316
Okay.

15:49.349 --> 15:50.917
Excuse us, will ya?

15:50.950 --> 15:51.818
Bye.

15:53.853 --> 15:55.622
What the hell?
You're blowing this!

15:55.655 --> 15:57.590
I'm sorry!
I'm freaking out, man.

15:57.624 --> 15:59.792
See, that's the problem with
your generation and the dating.

15:59.826 --> 16:01.128
That's what's wrong
with the --

16:01.161 --> 16:02.362
What do you call it,
the nay nay?

16:02.395 --> 16:03.430
The gray gray.

16:03.463 --> 16:05.298
The point is,
you always tell a woman

16:05.332 --> 16:06.599
up front
what you want,

16:06.633 --> 16:09.002
and that way, you don't
get into a pickle like this.

16:09.036 --> 16:11.204
You're right, Douglas.
You're always right.

16:11.238 --> 16:14.441
Yeah? Then why am I
striking out?

16:14.474 --> 16:16.509
Dude,
you want some advice?

16:16.543 --> 16:17.877
Yes.

16:17.910 --> 16:19.712
And the fact
that I'm allowing it

16:19.746 --> 16:21.548
is a personal
low point.

16:21.581 --> 16:23.983
Stop selling yourself.
Let her talk.

16:24.017 --> 16:26.153
You're obsessed
with this woman,

16:26.186 --> 16:27.387
but you don't know
anything about her.

16:27.420 --> 16:29.089
What's her name?

16:30.057 --> 16:31.358
I want to say Betty.

16:31.391 --> 16:33.126
Uh --
All right.

16:33.160 --> 16:34.961
Judy and I are gonna
head to the roller rink.

16:34.994 --> 16:37.130
It's the only place in the city
you can smoke indoors.

16:37.164 --> 16:41.234
Yo, um,
Douglas has a question.

16:41.268 --> 16:44.371
Forgive me, but in all the chaos
of this evening,

16:44.404 --> 16:45.905
I never caught
your name.

16:45.938 --> 16:47.507
Candace.

16:47.540 --> 16:50.643
Never Candy. Call me Candy,
I squash your grapes.

16:50.677 --> 16:52.245
Phenomenal woman.

16:53.213 --> 16:56.183
Hey. Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Where you going?

16:56.216 --> 16:57.417
I'm gonna find Zara.

16:57.450 --> 16:59.419
I'm gonna tell her
how I feel.

17:00.887 --> 17:02.822
[ Clicks tongue ]
How do I look?

17:02.855 --> 17:05.725
Ah, like a young
Steve McQueen.

17:05.758 --> 17:06.726
Cool.

17:06.759 --> 17:08.161
No idea.
I know.

17:08.195 --> 17:09.729
You look great.
Good luck.

17:09.762 --> 17:10.797
Thanks.

17:13.433 --> 17:15.902
So, Candace,
tell me about yourself.

17:15.935 --> 17:17.870
**

17:17.904 --> 17:19.406
We gotta watch it
one more time.
Oh, my God.

17:19.439 --> 17:21.040
Ah, I can't believe
we actually have this on video.

17:21.074 --> 17:22.342
Yes. Here.

17:22.375 --> 17:23.710
Hah!
And...

17:23.743 --> 17:24.877
Aah!
Frond! Ohh!Frond!

17:24.911 --> 17:27.447
Ow! It hurts!
It looks like it.

17:27.480 --> 17:29.015
It reminds me
of my first Korn concert.

17:29.048 --> 17:29.949
Ay-yi-yi.

17:29.982 --> 17:32.419
I got a combat boot
to the face.

17:32.452 --> 17:34.621
It's hardcore, okay?
That's the best story
I've ever heard.

17:34.654 --> 17:35.722
Let me get you
an ice pack.
[ Laughs ]

17:35.755 --> 17:36.823
Wait, Will.

17:38.325 --> 17:41.694
You were so different
out there in the storm.

17:41.728 --> 17:43.730
You were, like,
kind of a badass.

17:43.763 --> 17:46.899
Yeah, well, Lady Weather
is a ferocious mistress.

17:46.933 --> 17:47.967
Okay,
now you're ruining it.

17:48.000 --> 17:49.969
Okay.
What I mean is...

17:50.002 --> 17:52.305
[ Sighs ] I know you're trying
to play it safe with Sophie,

17:52.339 --> 17:55.908
but I bet she'd like
to see you like that.

17:55.942 --> 17:58.278
I think our kids
want to see us happy.

17:59.812 --> 18:00.647
Yeah.

18:00.680 --> 18:02.149
Yeah,
maybe you're right.

18:03.650 --> 18:05.452
Okay.

18:05.485 --> 18:06.453
By the way,

18:06.486 --> 18:08.288
did you have a thing
for The Beast?

18:08.321 --> 18:09.622
'Cause The Beast
was getting a vibe.

18:09.656 --> 18:10.790
All right, calm down.
Uh-huh.

18:10.823 --> 18:12.292
Let's watch me get hit
by the frond again.

18:12.325 --> 18:13.460
Okay. Yes, please.

18:13.493 --> 18:15.828
[ Sighing ] Oh, God.
All right. And...

18:15.862 --> 18:16.996
Aah!
Frond!Frond!

18:17.029 --> 18:18.831
It comes out of nowhere!

18:18.865 --> 18:20.400
We can laugh now
'cause we know you're okay.

18:20.433 --> 18:22.001
[ Chuckles ]

18:22.034 --> 18:23.570
You want some of those brownies
I made earlier?

18:23.603 --> 18:25.138
Yeah.

18:25.172 --> 18:27.974
These are burnt, but I think
if you cut into the center,

18:28.007 --> 18:29.008
they'll taste good.

18:29.041 --> 18:30.677
[ Laughs ]

18:30.710 --> 18:31.744
[ Feedback ]

18:31.778 --> 18:35.415
**

18:35.448 --> 18:37.317
Poppy,
go get him.

18:37.350 --> 18:39.619
[ Indistinct conversations ]

18:39.652 --> 18:41.954
Hi, I'm Poppy.

18:41.988 --> 18:43.256
Um, I don't know
if you remember,

18:43.290 --> 18:44.624
but we bumped into
each other earlier.

18:44.657 --> 18:46.125
[ Chuckles lightly ]
I was just wondering,

18:46.159 --> 18:47.994
maybe I could
buy you a drink?

18:48.027 --> 18:49.462
Yeah, I'd like that.

18:49.496 --> 18:51.030
But I'm just
about to go on.

18:51.063 --> 18:52.332
Oh. Yeah.

18:52.365 --> 18:53.700
After?

18:53.733 --> 18:54.634
Cool.

18:54.667 --> 18:56.803
[ Both chuckle ]

18:56.836 --> 18:58.538
How y'all doing out there
tonight?

18:58.571 --> 19:00.207
[ Applause ]

19:00.240 --> 19:02.675
This song goes out
to a woman I just met,

19:02.709 --> 19:05.044
who I feel like
I've known all my life.

19:06.979 --> 19:10.116
[ Slow music plays ]

19:10.149 --> 19:11.484
* I hate you, Mom

19:11.518 --> 19:12.885
* I hate you, Dad

19:12.919 --> 19:16.723
* And my step-mom, Karen

19:16.756 --> 19:18.325
* Karen, Karen, Karen, Karen

19:18.358 --> 19:19.892
* I don't understand

19:19.926 --> 19:21.561
Well, he's passionate.

19:21.594 --> 19:24.897
* Karen, why won't you let me
borrow your car? *

19:24.931 --> 19:27.367
Okay, we're outtie.
Let's go. We're walking.

19:27.400 --> 19:30.470
* Karen, I didn't spill
the juice on your white couch *

19:30.503 --> 19:32.004
* Mm, yeah

19:32.038 --> 19:33.640
[ Latin music playing ]

19:33.673 --> 19:42.815
**

19:42.849 --> 19:49.389
**

19:49.422 --> 19:51.190
[ Knock on door ]

19:51.224 --> 19:52.925
**

19:52.959 --> 19:55.061
Tony insisted
I bring you a plate.

19:55.094 --> 19:57.029
G-Good God.
Are you crying?

19:57.063 --> 19:59.366
No, I'm cool.

19:59.399 --> 20:05.605
**

20:05.638 --> 20:09.108
So, I can assume it didn't
go well with Zara, huh?

20:09.141 --> 20:11.678
[ Sighs ] I offered her
all I have --

20:11.711 --> 20:14.213
my heart.

20:14.247 --> 20:17.083
And we're gonna
co-parent Jack

20:17.116 --> 20:19.252
as two single adults
dating other people.

20:19.286 --> 20:21.254
At least now
I know where I stand.

20:21.288 --> 20:24.757
Well, women.
They'll rip you to shreds.

20:24.791 --> 20:26.693
So, how'd it go
with Big Red?

20:26.726 --> 20:28.127
Oh, she went home.

20:28.160 --> 20:30.297
After I told her
I had to cut the date short,

20:30.330 --> 20:33.800
she very slowly
nudged my glass of wine

20:33.833 --> 20:36.803
across and off the table.

20:36.836 --> 20:38.738
You know, like a cat.
Oh.

20:38.771 --> 20:40.440
Never loved her more.

20:40.473 --> 20:41.441
[ Chuckles ]

20:41.474 --> 20:42.542
So, what are
we drinking?

20:42.575 --> 20:44.444
Pedialyte.

20:44.477 --> 20:46.579
Hopefully
it'll help a hangover.

20:46.613 --> 20:48.315
Okay.

20:50.317 --> 20:51.484
[ Glasses clink ]

20:51.518 --> 20:53.420
Thanks, Douglas.

20:53.453 --> 20:54.454
You my road dawg.

20:54.487 --> 20:55.455
[ Pats back ]

20:55.488 --> 20:56.623
I get that right?

20:56.656 --> 20:57.824
Yeah, you did.

20:57.857 --> 20:59.326
Terrific.

21:00.960 --> 21:02.495
Ahh!
It's good, huh?

21:02.529 --> 21:04.364
No, it is not.

21:08.768 --> 21:09.736
So far, being single
ain't so bad.

21:09.769 --> 21:11.738
It's been an hour.
Give it time.

21:11.771 --> 21:14.006
You'll be
chasing lightning again.

21:14.040 --> 21:16.309
Never thought I'd say this,
but I get it.

21:16.343 --> 21:18.277
I had lightning
with that guy at the Winebrary

21:18.311 --> 21:19.278
until I didn't.

21:19.312 --> 21:20.480
But I'll keep looking,

21:20.513 --> 21:22.449
and next time,
it's gonna be real.

21:22.482 --> 21:25.318
Please.
That guy was a zero.

21:25.352 --> 21:28.087
Who's this guy, again?

21:28.120 --> 21:30.289
Oh, it's okay.
Just nudge him.

21:30.323 --> 21:32.959
**

21:32.992 --> 21:33.926
Harder.

21:33.960 --> 21:37.930
**

21:37.964 --> 21:39.366
Uh-oh.
